# AEM GraphQL Endpoint Configuration
# This example shows how to configure the Next.js app to fetch from AEM Content Fragments

# AEM Publish Host
# For AEM Cloud Service, use the publish instance URL pattern:
# https://publish-p<program>-e<env>.adobeaemcloud.com
# Example for acssandboxemea02jcadev:
NEXT_PUBLIC_AEM_HOST=https://publish-p<program-id>-e<env-id>.adobeaemcloud.com

# AEM GraphQL Endpoint path (typically fixed across instances)
NEXT_PUBLIC_AEM_GRAPHQL_ENDPOINT=/content/graphql/global/endpoint.json

# Optional: AEM Bearer token for authenticated requests
# Use this if your publish instance requires authentication
# NEXT_PUBLIC_AEM_AUTH=your-bearer-token-here

# Example live configuration for sandbox (uncomment and update <program-id> and <env-id>):
# NEXT_PUBLIC_AEM_HOST=https://publish-p<program-id>-e<env-id>.adobeaemcloud.com
# NEXT_PUBLIC_AEM_GRAPHQL_ENDPOINT=/content/graphql/global/endpoint.json
